21
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:50,840
{\fs17}What in Hades were you doing here anyway?

22
00:05:52,184 --> 00:05:56,211
{\fs17}I can't say that I've seen you around here before.

23
00:05:56,288 --> 00:06:00,247
{\fs17}No. If you're going to get yourself shot, do it where you're known.

24
00:06:09,301 --> 00:06:11,895
{\fs17}"Mr. Harry Worp,

25
00:06:11,970 --> 00:06:16,202
{\fs17}8 7 Maple Avenue, Boston, Massachusetts."

26
00:06:16,275 --> 00:06:19,938
{\fs17}Well, Worp, you're a long way from home.

27
00:06:20,012 --> 00:06:22,981
{\fs17}With the looks of it, you won't get back for Christmas. No.

28
00:06:25,717 --> 00:06:28,447
{\fs17}We're going to have a cold, hard winter.

29
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:32,183
{\fs17}Mmm. You might keep here a long time... an awful long time.

30
00:06:32,291 --> 00:06:34,418
{\fs17}Too long for me, Harry.

31
00:06:34,493 --> 00:06:36,427
{\fs17}Yes.

32
00:06:46,905 --> 00:06:49,339
{\fs17}Captain Wiles?

33
00:06:50,509 --> 00:06:52,477
{\fs17}Yes, ma'am?

34
00:06:56,114 --> 00:06:58,514
{\fs17}What seems to be the trouble, Captain?

35
00:06:58,550 --> 00:07:03,283
{\fs17}Well, it's what you might call an unavoidable accident.

36
00:07:03,355 --> 00:07:06,586
{\fs17}He's dead. Yes.

37
00:07:09,328 --> 00:07:13,492
{\fs17}I would say that he was. Of course, that's an unprofessional opinion.

38
00:07:13,565 --> 00:07:16,898
{\fs17}Yeah. Did you, uh... Did you know him, Miss Gravely?

39
00:07:16,968 --> 00:07:20,335
{\fs17}No. Doesn't live around here?

40
00:07:20,439 --> 00:07:24,398
{\fs17}Well, he died around here. That's what counts now. Embarrassing.

41
00:07:24,476 --> 00:07:28,242
{\fs17}What do you plan to do with him, Captain?

42
00:07:28,347 --> 00:07:33,649
{\fs17}Miss Gravely, without cutting the hem off truth garment,

43
00:07:33,752 --> 00:07:36,778
{\fs17}I'm gonna hide him, cover him up,

44
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:39,949
{\fs17}forget him.

45
00:07:41,860 --> 00:07:44,988
{\fs17}Are you never going to inform the police, Captain?

46
00:07:45,063 --> 00:07:48,226
{\fs17}No. Forget you saw me, Miss Gravely.

47
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:50,268
{\fs17}Chase it out of your mind, for heaven's sake.

48
00:07:50,302 --> 00:07:52,964
{\fs17}It was an accident. He was poking around the clearing...

49
00:07:53,071 --> 00:07:56,097
{\fs17}and I thought he was a rabbit or something.

50
00:07:56,174 --> 00:07:59,871
{\fs17}It was a human error. Ah, now, please, don't...

51
00:07:59,978 --> 00:08:03,243
{\fs17}Don't say anything to anybody, Miss Gravely.

52
00:08:04,916 --> 00:08:07,578
{\fs17}Do as you think best, Captain.

53
00:08:07,686 --> 00:08:10,678
{\fs17}I'm sure you must have met many similar situations...

54
00:08:10,789 --> 00:08:13,019
{\fs17}in your travels in foreign lands.

55
00:08:13,091 --> 00:08:15,355
{\fs17}Yeah. I've seen much worse things.

56
00:08:15,427 --> 00:08:17,395
{\fs17}I certainly won't say anything. Much worse things.

57
00:08:17,429 --> 00:08:19,556
{\fs17}I remember when I was on the Orinoco.

58
00:08:19,631 --> 00:08:21,599
{\fs17}We had a Turk, a great, big Turk there...

59
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,601
{\fs17}running amuck with a machete.

60
00:08:23,635 --> 00:08:26,331
{\fs17}Captain, if I were going to hide an accident, I shouldn't delay.

61
00:08:26,405 --> 00:08:31,206
{\fs17}Oh. Oh. You're right as rain, Miss Gravely.

62
00:08:31,309 --> 00:08:35,006
{\fs17}Yes. You know something? I'm glad I met you today.

63
00:08:35,113 --> 00:08:38,014
{\fs17}I feel better for telling somebody as warm,

64
00:08:38,116 --> 00:08:42,519
{\fs17}tender, understanding as yourself.

65
00:08:42,621 --> 00:08:46,751
{\fs17}Well, on the contrary, Captain. It...

66
00:08:46,825 --> 00:08:52,161
{\fs17}It... I'm certainly glad if I helped you, Captain.

67
00:08:52,230 --> 00:08:55,358
{\fs17}Perhaps you would care to come over for some blueberry muffins...

68
00:08:55,434 --> 00:08:58,835
{\fs17}and coffee later on... high-bush blueberries?

69
00:08:58,870 --> 00:09:01,430
{\fs17}Ah, well. This is certainly something of an interesting surprise.

70
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:04,202
{\fs17}And perhaps a touch of elderberry wine. Oh.

71
00:09:04,276 --> 00:09:08,440
{\fs17}After all, we've been neighbors for nearly three years now...

72
