89
00:10:33,665 --> 00:10:37,533
{\fs17}A deep wonderful sleep...How did he heat his head?

90
00:10:37,636 --> 00:10:39,934
{\fs17}Putting it where it wasn't wanted would be my guess.

91
00:10:40,038 --> 00:10:42,939
{\fs17}- Will it get better? - Not if we're lucky.

92
00:10:44,676 --> 00:10:47,236
{\fs17}Let's run home and I'll make you some lemonade.

93
00:10:47,345 --> 00:10:50,837
{\fs17}Will lemonade put me in a wonderful, deep, deep sleep, Mommy?

94
00:10:50,949 --> 00:10:54,680
{\fs17}- No, Arnie, but it's better than no lemonade. - I don't understand that.

95
00:10:54,753 --> 00:10:56,846
{\fs17}Never mind. Now, you just forget you ever saw this man.

96
00:10:56,955 --> 00:10:58,855
{\fs17}Is there a special way to forget?

97
00:10:58,957 --> 00:11:02,358
{\fs17}Just think of something else. I think I'll try not to see him tomorrow, Mommy.

98
00:11:02,394 --> 00:11:06,160
{\fs17}That's a good boy, Arnie. Now, let's run home and get that lemonade.

99
00:11:08,366 --> 00:11:11,267
{\fs17}She won't care what I do with him.

