149
00:16:25,783 --> 00:16:29,378
{\fs17}He sells 'em. Mechanical antiques. Doesn't make much, but he needs the money.

150
00:16:32,991 --> 00:16:35,892
{\fs17}Hmm. Doesn't he get paid for being deputy sheriff?

151
00:16:35,994 --> 00:16:38,895
{\fs17}Piecework. Gets paid by the arrest, I think.

152
00:16:42,033 --> 00:16:44,558
{\fs17}Ah, Mr. Marlow. It's wonderful.

153
00:16:48,406 --> 00:16:52,809
{\fs17}I've been in a tortured mood lately. What is it?

154
00:16:52,911 --> 00:16:55,471
{\fs17}Good old Wiggy, my sternest critic.

155
00:16:55,546 --> 00:16:58,014
{\fs17}Even if I don't understand your work, I think it's beautiful.

156
00:16:58,116 --> 00:17:00,016
{\fs17}So does Mrs. Rogers.

157
00:17:00,118 --> 00:17:02,518
{\fs17}Oh? You talk about me? Well, l...

158
00:17:02,620 --> 00:17:04,679
